Let's think step by step. To find the sum $S=f(1)+f(2)+\cdots+f(1985)$, we need to find each term in the sequence recursively using the given recurrence relation. By the hint, we know the recurrence relation is $f(n+1)=-f(n)+(-1)^{n+1}(n+1)$. Using this, we can find the first few terms:
\begin{align*}
f(1)&=f(1)=f(1)=1\\
f(2)&=-\left(f(1)\right)+(-1)^{2}(2)=\boxed{-1}\\
f(3)&=-\left(f(2)\right)+(-1)^{3}(3)=\boxed{2}\\
&\;\;\;\vdots \\
f(1985)&=\underbrace{-\left(\cdots -\left(-\left(f(1984)\right)\right)\right.\right.}_{\text{1984 times}}+\underbrace{(-1)^{1985}(1985)}_{\text{last term}}
\end{align*}
